WEBVTT

00:02.710 --> 00:04.080
Dre: There was a time
 not that long ago when women

00:04.080 --> 00:06.580
could celebrate
 their pregnancies openly.

00:06.580 --> 00:10.080
Sometimes even
 with cigarettes and drinks.

00:10.080 --> 00:12.580
But nowadays, for many women
 in the workforce,

00:12.580 --> 00:14.790
there's a concern
 that being pregnant

00:14.790 --> 00:17.120
could hurt
 their career trajectory.

00:17.120 --> 00:19.500
So, they try to hide it.

00:19.500 --> 00:21.500
How about now?
Do I still look pregnant?

00:21.500 --> 00:22.540
Yes.

00:22.540 --> 00:24.620
♪♪

00:24.620 --> 00:26.040
How about now?

00:27.040 --> 00:29.830
You look like a table
at El Torito...

00:29.830 --> 00:31.120
that's pregnant.

00:33.120 --> 00:34.580
Of course,
 Bow had a good reason

00:34.580 --> 00:37.120
for hiding her pregnancy
 at work.

00:37.120 --> 00:39.500
She's in the running to be
 a partner in her practice.

00:39.500 --> 00:40.880
[ Ding! ]

00:40.880 --> 00:42.880
And her competition is tough.

00:42.880 --> 00:44.250
It's between me
and Holiday Hannah.

00:44.250 --> 00:46.790
Who?
 Holiday Hannah, Dre.

00:46.790 --> 00:48.420
I know it's Halloween,

00:48.420 --> 00:51.290
but we need somebody
to cover the E.R. tonight.

00:51.290 --> 00:53.540
I don't have kids.
I can do it.

00:53.540 --> 00:55.210
I know
it's Valentine's Day,

00:55.210 --> 00:57.670
but we need somebody
to work the E.R. tonight.

00:57.670 --> 00:59.920
I don't have a boyfriend.
I can do it.

00:59.920 --> 01:01.540
I know it's Mother's Day,

01:01.540 --> 01:03.960
but we need somebody
to cover the E.R. tonight.

01:03.960 --> 01:06.120
My mother's dead.

01:06.120 --> 01:08.080
I can do it.
 Wha...

01:08.080 --> 01:10.540
And so far,
 Bow's been successful

01:10.540 --> 01:12.960
in hiding the pregnancy
 from her potential partners.

01:15.830 --> 01:18.380
Dr. Stone, hey.
 Hi.

01:18.380 --> 01:19.670
Gosh,
I'm so looking forward

01:19.670 --> 01:21.420
to sitting down with you
and the partners tomorrow.

01:21.420 --> 01:22.920
So are we. You have a lot
of fans in that room.

01:22.920 --> 01:23.920
Oh, good to know.

01:23.920 --> 01:25.170
[ Laughing ] Thank you.
 [ Alarms beeping ]

01:25.170 --> 01:26.170
You look beautiful today.

01:26.170 --> 01:27.960
Man: Code blue. Code blue.

01:27.960 --> 01:29.120
Patient in 103
is coding.

01:29.120 --> 01:30.120
I need this.

01:30.120 --> 01:31.420
Yeah, I need it, too.
Okay.

01:31.420 --> 01:32.420
Okay.
 Bow?

01:32.420 --> 01:33.580
Yes?
 Doctor?

01:33.580 --> 01:34.920
Coding.
 Oh, you said coding.

01:34.920 --> 01:35.960
Yes!
 Okay.

01:35.960 --> 01:36.960
Thank you.
 Get out of here.

01:36.960 --> 01:37.750
You are to go! Go!

01:38.920 --> 01:41.080
Oh!
I'm pregnant!

01:41.080 --> 01:41.960
[ Laughs ]

01:41.960 --> 01:43.120
Congratulations.

01:43.120 --> 01:45.500
Thank you so much.
I -- Yep.

01:45.500 --> 01:47.000
Well, I will
see you tomorrow.

01:47.000 --> 01:49.540
I'll see you tomorrow.
I can't wait.

01:49.540 --> 01:51.040
I can't wait.

01:51.040 --> 01:52.290
He didn't make it.
 Really?

01:52.290 --> 01:54.000
Hey,
congratulations.

01:55.580 --> 01:56.710
Thanks, Larry.

01:56.710 --> 01:59.540
Circle of life.
Pbht! Hooray!

01:59.540 --> 02:00.540
♪♪

02:08.460 --> 02:11.670
Dre: So, Bow's pregnancy
 was affecting everyone.

02:11.670 --> 02:13.080
Dre?
 Hmm?

02:13.080 --> 02:14.120
What are you doing?

02:14.120 --> 02:16.210
Oh, man,
I got a pregnant wife at home,

02:16.210 --> 02:19.040
and I am gonna be a hero
at 3:00 a.m.

02:19.040 --> 02:20.420
with these tiny pickles.

02:20.420 --> 02:22.580
These are also for Bow,
as well.

02:23.540 --> 02:25.290
Must be nice having a wife,
you know,

02:25.290 --> 02:27.960
someone you can
share secrets with,

02:27.960 --> 02:29.880
just anything tethering you
to this world.

02:29.880 --> 02:32.250
You're not a danger to others,
just yourself, right?

02:32.250 --> 02:34.830
So, Dre, are you gonna
take paternity leave
when the baby comes?

02:34.830 --> 02:37.290
"Paternity leave"? Huh!

02:37.290 --> 02:39.330
He meant
"paternity test," Dre.

02:39.330 --> 02:40.880
Oh, I know it's mine.
I was there.

02:40.880 --> 02:42.710
Oh, my man.
My man.

02:42.710 --> 02:44.540
No. No. I mean, are
you gonna stay home and
take care of your baby?

02:44.540 --> 02:46.500
[ Laughter ]

02:46.500 --> 02:47.330
Stevens: That's a good one.

02:48.460 --> 02:51.080
It's so crazy!

02:51.080 --> 02:53.540
Daddy, can you imagine if you
stayed home to take care of me?

02:53.540 --> 02:56.000
[ Laughs ] I can't.
I really can't. I mean...

02:56.000 --> 02:58.790
Besides, this whole
paternity thing, it's not real.

02:58.790 --> 03:00.500
I mean, there's nothing
a man can do

03:00.500 --> 03:01.750
to help a woman
with a baby.

03:01.750 --> 03:03.040
He can't nurse.

03:03.040 --> 03:05.210
He can't go
to doctor's appointments.

03:05.210 --> 03:07.750
I mean, what's a man gonna do
with a baby? Hold it?

03:07.750 --> 03:09.420
[ Laughter ]

03:09.420 --> 03:11.960
What would that even look like?
What would it look like?

03:11.960 --> 03:13.960
Where do you --
Hold on. Hold on.

03:13.960 --> 03:16.580
So, you had four kids and you
weren't home with any of them?

03:16.580 --> 03:20.040
Well, no. I stayed home
after Zoey was born.

03:20.040 --> 03:22.210
But that's because
I was unemployed.

03:22.210 --> 03:24.830
Yes! It's okay for a man
to be unemployed.

03:24.830 --> 03:26.540
There's nobility
in the struggle.

03:26.540 --> 03:28.580
You remember, Connie.
 Connor: How could I forget?

03:28.580 --> 03:30.620
I was lying on the couch
in my Snuggie,

03:30.620 --> 03:32.920
eating a muffin,
and then you came in and told me

03:32.920 --> 03:34.420
that I could work here.
 Wow.

03:34.420 --> 03:37.170
The proudest moment
of my life, Buttercup.

03:37.170 --> 03:39.210
Yeah.
 You see?
Paternity leave.

03:39.210 --> 03:42.290
I never took it
and Connie turned out just fine.

03:42.290 --> 03:45.790
Uh, Connie wears
a house-arrest anklet.

03:45.790 --> 03:47.170
But only
for two more weeks.

03:47.170 --> 03:49.210
What?
 Charlie: Eustace
turned out great, too.

03:49.210 --> 03:50.460
He's so independent,

03:50.460 --> 03:53.170
I don't know where he is
half the time.

03:53.170 --> 03:55.380
Like now.

03:55.380 --> 03:57.420
Eustace!

04:01.080 --> 04:05.290
♪♪

04:05.290 --> 04:08.670
Hey. Has anyone seen
my iPod Shuffle?

04:08.670 --> 04:10.290
Excuse me.
 Hey, hey.

04:10.290 --> 04:11.290
Hey. Ouch.
 Listen, listen, listen.

04:11.290 --> 04:12.420
It's gone missing.

04:12.420 --> 04:14.580
Are you hearing me?

04:14.580 --> 04:17.620
I'm talking about
an iPod Shuffle.

04:17.620 --> 04:20.120
The greatest piece
of non-vibrating technology

04:20.120 --> 04:22.079
the world has ever seen.

04:22.079 --> 04:24.620
Do they still make
iPod Shuffles?

04:24.620 --> 04:25.830
Huh?
 What's it look like?

04:25.830 --> 04:28.540
It looks like
a tiny little square.

04:28.540 --> 04:31.830
And I can't power-walk through
the Crenshaw Mall without it.

04:31.830 --> 04:33.750
Can't you just use
your Tae Bo videos

04:33.750 --> 04:35.380
or your Shake Weight?

04:35.380 --> 04:38.290
What do mean?
To, like, exercise with?

04:38.290 --> 04:40.250
Hi, Ruby.

04:40.250 --> 04:43.670
Ah, I love the track suit
and kitten heels.

04:43.670 --> 04:47.920
Yeah, listen, you haven't seen
my iPod Shuffle, have you?

04:47.920 --> 04:50.290
I'm sorry. I haven't.
But I'll keep an eye out.

04:50.290 --> 04:52.120
Uh-huh.

04:52.120 --> 04:54.210
Yeah.

04:54.210 --> 04:56.250
Children.

04:56.250 --> 04:57.960
Children, gather.

04:57.960 --> 04:59.460
Gather quickly.

05:01.620 --> 05:04.540
We have a thief
in the house.

05:04.540 --> 05:07.080
Vivian stole my Shuffle.

05:07.080 --> 05:09.380
What? Grandma,
nobody would steal that.

05:09.380 --> 05:11.380
Oh, that's crazy.
 You see, the struggle is always
real for you.

05:11.380 --> 05:14.540
This isn't the first time Vivian
has stolen from me.

05:14.540 --> 05:17.580
♪♪

05:20.080 --> 05:22.790
I'm not sure
that counts as stealing.

05:22.790 --> 05:26.290
Yeah. Also Vivian
is very pretty, so...

05:26.290 --> 05:28.500
Hm.
I never liked her.

05:28.500 --> 05:29.710
I'm on board.

05:29.710 --> 05:31.670
Very wise, Diane.

05:31.670 --> 05:33.380
Yes, yes.

05:33.380 --> 05:35.460
Oh,
we gonna find that Shuffle.

05:35.460 --> 05:38.250
Dre: So, Bow had her interview
 with the partners,

05:38.250 --> 05:40.620
and since there was an elephant
 in the room,

05:40.620 --> 05:42.170
she tried to lighten the mood.

05:42.170 --> 05:45.080
Well, I am glad that you guys
have your coffee

05:45.080 --> 05:48.000
'cause I am such
a good anesthesiologist,

05:48.000 --> 05:49.290
I might put you
to sleep.

05:49.290 --> 05:51.710
[ Laughter ]

05:51.710 --> 05:52.960
'Cause I know how to...

05:52.960 --> 05:54.710
Oh, womp.
[ Laughs ]

05:54.710 --> 05:56.540
[ Ding! ]
  And failed.

05:56.540 --> 05:59.170
But then she dealt
 with the elephant head on.

05:59.170 --> 06:01.250
Being pregnant is an asset.

06:01.250 --> 06:02.920
It means I'm completely loyal.

06:02.920 --> 06:05.580
The baby is not gonna interfere
with my schedule at all.

06:05.580 --> 06:09.000
I will be back in six weeks.
[ Chuckles ]

06:10.210 --> 06:12.670
Pregnant women can do it all.

06:12.670 --> 06:14.920
Meanwhile,
 I was realizing that Josh

06:14.920 --> 06:17.290
might not be wrong
 about paternity leave.

06:17.290 --> 06:19.750
I mean, I wasn't home
 after Junior was born.

06:19.750 --> 06:20.880
Have you seen my wand?

06:20.880 --> 06:22.750
I can't find it
anywhere,

06:22.750 --> 06:24.750
and my spell book
is useless without it.

06:24.750 --> 06:27.000
And I didn't stay home
 with the twins, either.

06:27.000 --> 06:29.170
Hey, Dad --
Ohh!

06:29.170 --> 06:32.330
I am not taking care of him
when we're adults.

06:32.330 --> 06:33.920
Or you, Dad.

06:33.920 --> 06:35.580
I hope
you've invested well.

06:35.580 --> 06:36.710
What?

06:36.710 --> 06:38.000
Ow!

06:38.000 --> 06:39.500
Uh...

06:39.500 --> 06:42.040
But then there's Zoey.

06:42.040 --> 06:44.250
[ Ethereal music plays ]

06:44.250 --> 06:45.330
She's perfect.

06:45.330 --> 06:47.540
Oh, morning, Dad.

06:47.540 --> 06:48.920
Good morning, baby girl.

06:48.920 --> 06:51.080
O-M-G, did you see
that video online?

06:51.080 --> 06:53.460
Yeah, with the goat
and the baby throwing up?

06:53.460 --> 06:55.040
Both: At the same time.

06:55.040 --> 06:56.380
Mm!

06:56.380 --> 06:59.170
We have the same
 sense of humor, same style.

06:59.170 --> 07:00.790
Wait.

07:00.790 --> 07:03.420
What if Zoey turned out
 so great because I was home

07:03.420 --> 07:06.290
during the first crucial months
 of her life?

07:06.290 --> 07:07.710
I knew what I had to do.

07:07.710 --> 07:09.210
Ow!

07:09.210 --> 07:11.080
Ooh.

07:11.080 --> 07:12.710
Why are you still
on the floor?

07:16.420 --> 07:17.920
Hey, guys, guys.

07:17.920 --> 07:19.040
Seriously, it's time to get
into this Bailey's campaign.

07:19.040 --> 07:20.790
Now remember,
they want it to be seen

07:20.790 --> 07:23.000
as something more
than just a holiday drink.

07:23.000 --> 07:25.290
So let us brainstorm.
Go.

07:25.290 --> 07:26.920
Uh, okay, winter.

07:26.920 --> 07:28.670
Uh, skiing.
 Mm-hmm.

07:28.670 --> 07:30.210
Shooting wolves
from a helicopter.

07:30.210 --> 07:31.670
Nice. Go ahead.

07:31.670 --> 07:33.460
Long bath
with a short woman.
 Mm.

07:33.460 --> 07:36.000
Or I mean deep bath
with a shallow woman.

07:36.000 --> 07:37.750
Weird but wonderful.
Go ahead.

07:37.750 --> 07:39.960
Sitting by the fire,
waiting for the phone to ring.

07:39.960 --> 07:42.500
Oh, for God's sake.
Just take the shot, Josh.

07:42.500 --> 07:44.000
Oh.
 Dre, come on.

07:44.000 --> 07:45.960
I'm taking
paternity leave.

07:45.960 --> 07:47.460
Okay, that makes no sense.

07:47.460 --> 07:48.830
See, we're looking
for words that actually
help with the product,

07:48.830 --> 07:50.670
like indulgent,
deliciously perfect --

07:50.670 --> 07:51.920
No.

07:51.920 --> 07:54.420
I'm taking
paternity leave.

07:54.420 --> 07:56.120
What?
 Nice! Hey!

07:56.120 --> 07:58.000
I told you
he was gay, Dad.

07:58.000 --> 07:59.250
Shh! That's, uh --

07:59.250 --> 08:00.710
That's text talk,
kitten.

08:00.710 --> 08:02.790
Okay,
I've done some research.

08:02.790 --> 08:04.790
And did you know
that when babies are born,

08:04.790 --> 08:06.170
they resemble
their fathers?

08:06.170 --> 08:09.000
It's Mother Nature's way
of keeping the dads invested.

08:09.000 --> 08:10.670
I was disappointed
when Eustace

08:10.670 --> 08:12.670
looked more like my brother,
Eustace.

08:12.670 --> 08:13.500
Mm.

08:14.540 --> 08:16.830
Eustace!

08:18.080 --> 08:20.210
Look, Dre, if paternity leave
was so great,

08:20.210 --> 08:21.750
why wouldn't everyone
be taking it?

08:21.750 --> 08:23.500
Around the world,
they do.

08:23.500 --> 08:27.790
In Denmark, more than 90%
of dads take time off.

08:27.790 --> 08:29.290
Mm.
 Connor:
Denmark. Please.

08:29.290 --> 08:30.420
What has Denmark
ever done?

08:30.420 --> 08:31.710
Uh, Legos.

08:31.710 --> 08:33.080
Legoland.

08:33.080 --> 08:34.580
Wait.
They made Legos?

08:34.580 --> 08:35.919
Wow.
 Legos, Legos?

08:35.919 --> 08:38.039
Okay, okay, look, guys,
the point is

08:38.039 --> 08:39.830
I want to give my baby
the best chance in life.

08:39.830 --> 08:41.789
That way Zoey
and the baby

08:41.789 --> 08:43.750
can take care of
all the middle ones.

08:43.750 --> 08:46.540
I'm proud of you,
my brother.

08:46.540 --> 08:48.080
Put your hand down,
Josh.

08:48.080 --> 08:49.330
Of course.

08:49.330 --> 08:50.750
Stevens: Seriously,
just take the shot.

08:53.040 --> 08:54.420
Hey, babe.
 Hey, babe.

08:54.420 --> 08:57.250
So, uh,
how'd your interview go?

08:57.250 --> 08:59.710
It's interesting you should ask,
my darling.

08:59.710 --> 09:01.040
Mm?
 You know why?

09:01.040 --> 09:02.290
Why?

09:02.290 --> 09:03.420
Because I nailed it.

09:03.420 --> 09:05.920
[ Laughs ]
 I nailed it!

09:05.920 --> 09:07.250
I mean, it was a little bit
awkward at first.

09:07.250 --> 09:09.170
Mm-hmm.
 And then I nailed it, Dre.

09:09.170 --> 09:10.330
I super nailed it.

09:10.330 --> 09:12.460
I'm so proud of you.

09:12.460 --> 09:13.750
Thank you, baby.
 Yep.

09:13.750 --> 09:15.420
I also killed it today.

09:15.420 --> 09:16.210
Really?
 Mm-hmm.

09:16.210 --> 09:17.330
What'd you do?

09:17.330 --> 09:18.670
I'm taking
paternity leave.

09:20.670 --> 09:22.920
What?! Oh, my --
Dre, that's fantastic.

09:22.920 --> 09:24.790
Mm-hmm.
 I -- I didn't even know
you were thinking about that.

09:24.790 --> 09:27.290
I want my baby
to have all the benefits

09:27.290 --> 09:29.620
of a strong,
present father.

09:29.620 --> 09:30.920
Oh, you're the best.

09:30.920 --> 09:32.540
And if you time it right,

09:32.540 --> 09:33.920
I can go
to the NBA Finals.

09:33.920 --> 09:35.170
Dre.
 Mm-hmm.

09:35.170 --> 09:37.540
So, DeVonté, you keep kicking
and you keep cooking.

09:37.540 --> 09:39.580
Great. Okay.
 Mm, my baby.

09:39.580 --> 09:41.380
My baby nailed it.
 I nailed it.

09:41.380 --> 09:43.120
I totally nailed it.
 Mm!

09:43.120 --> 09:44.790
Jack: Grandma.
 Ruby: Mm?

09:44.790 --> 09:46.120
You were right.

09:46.120 --> 09:48.040
My Robotruck
is definitely missing.

09:48.040 --> 09:49.880
And I can't find
my favorite crop top.

09:49.880 --> 09:51.250
I've looked
everywhere.

09:51.250 --> 09:52.750
Are you sure
it could be Vivian?

09:52.750 --> 09:55.120
It could, and it is.

09:55.120 --> 09:56.960
It's just so hard
to believe.

09:56.960 --> 09:58.880
It's easy to believe
if you accept the fact

09:58.880 --> 10:01.460
that people are inherently evil,
which I do.

10:01.460 --> 10:03.790
Okay, I can't sit by
any longer

10:03.790 --> 10:06.960
and let you all slander
Vivian's good name.

10:06.960 --> 10:09.710
I present to you
exhibit "A".

10:09.710 --> 10:12.040
Does this look like
a thief to you?

10:12.040 --> 10:13.290
Or this?

10:13.290 --> 10:16.290
Ew.
Are these stalker photos?

10:16.290 --> 10:18.460
No.
They're candids.
 Of her butt?

10:18.460 --> 10:21.750
All this proves is you won't
be able to live near a school.

10:21.750 --> 10:24.710
Now, listen up.
Vivian is the perfect thief.

10:24.710 --> 10:26.880
She has complete access.

10:26.880 --> 10:29.670
We don't even pat her down
when she leaves.

10:29.670 --> 10:31.330
Oh, my God.
 Yeah.

10:31.330 --> 10:32.580
You're right.
 Uh-huh.

10:32.580 --> 10:34.040
What fools we've been.

10:34.040 --> 10:36.000
It's time to remember
the golden rule.

10:36.000 --> 10:40.000
When someone steals from you,
catch them.

10:40.000 --> 10:41.710
And shame them.

10:41.710 --> 10:43.790
That's not the gold--

10:43.790 --> 10:46.120
I said...

10:46.120 --> 10:47.830
shame them.

10:47.830 --> 10:49.000
Preach.

10:49.000 --> 10:50.880
♪♪

10:50.880 --> 10:52.960
And the Bailey's account
will go to Charlie.

10:52.960 --> 10:54.380
Hey.

10:54.380 --> 10:56.710
Hey!
Bailey's is mine!

10:56.710 --> 10:58.330
Oh, hey, Dre.

10:58.330 --> 11:00.620
[ Whispers indistinctly ]

11:00.620 --> 11:01.830
Oh, yeah.

11:01.830 --> 11:04.580
Um, I would like
to formally apologize

11:04.580 --> 11:06.960
for sending out
that company-wide e-mail

11:06.960 --> 11:08.880
calling your plan
to take paternity leave

11:08.880 --> 11:10.960
"bitch stuff."
 [ Chuckles ]

11:10.960 --> 11:13.790
But on the plus side,
it did prompt a pop-in visit

11:13.790 --> 11:17.080
from our HR executive,
who is a woman.

11:17.080 --> 11:19.460
Again,
my name is Rachel.

11:19.460 --> 11:22.620
And I feel like you really
don't get why I'm here.

11:22.620 --> 11:23.460
Because you're hot,
sweetheart.

11:23.460 --> 11:25.290
[ Light laughter ]

11:25.290 --> 11:26.290
[ Whispers indistinctly ]

11:26.290 --> 11:27.710
Right.

11:27.710 --> 11:29.750
That was inappropriate.

11:29.750 --> 11:32.960
And you may also
take paternity leave.

11:32.960 --> 11:36.290
Thank you for doing what
is legally required of you.

11:36.290 --> 11:38.210
Actually, you know, Dre,
we crunched the numbers.

11:38.210 --> 11:40.580
With you not here,
we save a ton on food.

11:40.580 --> 11:42.540
